window.__QUIZ_DATA__=[{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>1","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"PRODUCTION : FACTORS OF PRODUCTION","question":"A firm which turns timber into wooden office desks belongs to the","images":[],"options":{"A":"extractive industry","B":"direct service industry","C":"indirect service industry","D":"construction industry"},"answer":"D","explanation":"While it might seem like manufacturing, in the broader context, especially in relation to sectors directly dealing with physical goods and their utilization, such firms are often categorized under the construction industry. This is because they produce items used in the construction of office spaces and other buildings.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>2","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: ADVERTISING : TYPES AND MEDIA","question":"E-commerce is an activity which involves","images":[],"options":{"A":"trading in products through the post office","B":"trading in products through the internet","C":"buying and selling of products through telegram messages","D":"buying and selling of products through fax messages"},"answer":"B","explanation":"E-commerce refers to the buying and selling of goods or services using the internet, and the transfer of money and data to execute these transactions. Therefore, the correct answer is 'trading in products through the internet'.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>3","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS CAPITAL, PROFIT AND TURNOVER : SOURCE OF FINANCE","question":"Rent is the return on","images":[],"options":{"A":"a loan","B":"labour","C":"land","D":"a share"},"answer":"C","explanation":"In economics, rent is the income derived from the ownership of land and other rental properties. It is the return on land. Therefore, the correct answer is 'land'.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>4","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS UNIT: PARTNERSHIP : MEANING AND TYPES","question":"A partner whose only contribution to the partnership is his name and goodwill is","images":[],"options":{"A":"an active partner","B":"a limited partner","C":"a nominal partner","D":"a sleeping partner"},"answer":"C","explanation":"A nominal partner is a partner who does not invest any capital or share in the profits or losses of a business, but lends his name to the firm. His name gives the firm a certain reputation and goodwill. This is different from an active partner who takes part in the management of the business, a limited partner who has limited liability and a sleeping partner who invests capital but does not participate in the management.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>5","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"TRADE ASSOCIATION : MEANING & FUNCTIONS","question":"Computer manufacturers in an area could form a","images":[],"options":{"A":"producer association","B":"thrift society","C":"chamber of commerce","D":"consumer association"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Computer manufacturers in an area could form a producer association. A producer association is a group of manufacturers or businesses that produce similar products or services and come together to collaborate on business matters, such as setting standards, sharing research, or lobbying government. This is different from a thrift society which is a savings and loan organization, a chamber of commerce which is a network of local businesses, or a consumer association which is a group that advocates for consumer rights.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>6","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"TRADE : HOME TRADE: RETAIL TRADE","question":"The problem of double coincidence of wants is that","images":[],"options":{"A":"it is hard to determine the exchange rate for goods","B":"it does not encourage purchase of large quantities and varieties","C":"deferred payment is not possible because goods exchanged are not durable","D":"one has to find someone who wants his surplus and also has what he needs"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The problem of double coincidence of wants refers to the difficulty in barter trade where one has to find someone who wants his surplus and also has what he needs. This is because in barter trade, for a transaction to occur, both parties must desire what the other has to offer. This is different from the other options which refer to other problems associated with barter trade such as determining the exchange rate for goods, encouraging purchase of large quantities and varieties, or making deferred payment possible.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>7","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS UNIT: PUBLIC CORPORATION : MEANING AND TYPES","question":"The type of business where management is separated from ownership is a","images":[],"options":{"A":"sole proprietorship","B":"public company","C":"partnership","D":"cooperative society"},"answer":"B","explanation":"A public company is a type of business where management is separated from ownership. This is because the owners (shareholders) do not participate in the day-to-day running of the company. Instead, they elect a board of directors to manage the company on their behalf.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>8","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS UNIT: PARTNERSHIP : FEATURES AND IMPORTANCE","question":"Where there is no deed of partnership, members share profit on","images":[],"options":{"A":"the basis of participation","B":"the basis of shares held","C":"patronage basis","D":"equal basis"},"answer":"D","explanation":"In the absence of a partnership deed, the law assumes that all partners share profits and losses equally, regardless of their capital contribution or level of involvement in the business. This is a legal principle in partnership law.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>9","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"PRODUCTION : FACTORS OF PRODUCTION","question":"The factor of production that is fixed in nature is","images":[],"options":{"A":"land","B":"labour","C":"entrepreneurship","D":"capital"},"answer":"A","explanation":"In the context of economics, land is considered a fixed factor of production. This is because the quantity of land is fixed and cannot be increased or decreased by human effort. It includes all natural resources that are used in the production process.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>10","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: BANKING : SERVICES & CHALLENGES","question":"A means of payment through the post office is","images":[],"options":{"A":"standing order","B":"money order","C":"debit card","D":"credit card"},"answer":"B","explanation":"A means of payment through the post office is a money order. A money order is a payment order for a specific amount of money. It is more trusted than a cheque as it is prepaid. The money is received by the post office at the time of issuance.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>11","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"OCCUPATION : TYPES OF OCCUPATION","question":"A stock exchange broker is engaged in","images":[],"options":{"A":"construction occupation","B":"commercial occupation","C":"extractive occupation","D":"manufacturing occupation"},"answer":"B","explanation":"A stock exchange broker is engaged in a commercial occupation. They are involved in buying and selling of securities on behalf of their clients on the stock exchange. This is a commercial activity as it involves trade and commerce.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>12","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS UNIT: MERGER : MEANING AND TYPES OF MERGER","question":"A group of companies formed to carry out an activity that is beyond the ability of any individual company is","images":[],"options":{"A":"a subsidiary","B":"a merger","C":"a consortium","D":"an acquisition"},"answer":"C","explanation":"A group of companies formed to carry out an activity that is beyond the ability of any individual company is a consortium. A consortium is an association of two or more companies, organizations, or governments (or any combination of these entities) with the objective of participating in a common activity or pooling their resources for achieving a common goal.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>13","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS CAPITAL, PROFIT AND TURNOVER : TYPES OF CAPITAL","question":"The share capital of a company stated in the Memorandum of Association and approved by the registrar of companies is","images":[],"options":{"A":"working capital","B":"paid-up capital","C":"nominal capital","D":"called-up capital"},"answer":"C","explanation":"The share capital of a company stated in the Memorandum of Association and approved by the registrar of companies is the nominal capital. Nominal capital, also known as authorized capital, is the maximum amount of share capital that a company is authorized to issue to shareholders. It is a notional value and the company may not issue the entire amount of nominal capital.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>14","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"TRADE ASSOCIATION : OBJECTIVES , MERIT & DEMERIT","question":"One of the aims of a trade association is to","images":[],"options":{"A":"liaise with other trade associations in other countries","B":"organize trade fairs and exhibitions","C":"provide quality goods and services","D":"promote commercial activities in their business"},"answer":"D","explanation":"One of the aims of a trade association is to promote commercial activities in their business. Trade associations are organizations founded and funded by businesses that operate in a specific industry. They participate in public relations activities such as advertising, education, political donations, lobbying and publishing, but their main focus is collaboration between companies, or standardization.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>15","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"TRADE : HOME TRADE: RETAIL TRADE","question":"Retail outlets which sell from vehicles are","images":[],"options":{"A":"supermarkets","B":"mobile shops","C":"departmental stores","D":"chain stores"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Retail outlets which sell from vehicles are mobile shops. Mobile shops are a type of retail outlet that operates from a vehicle or moving transport. They are able to change their location and serve customers in different areas, providing convenience and accessibility.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>16","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS CAPITAL, PROFIT AND TURNOVER : SOURCE OF FINANCE","question":"Cash in hand and at bank, plus debtors are components of","images":[],"options":{"A":"intangible assets","B":"current assets","C":"current liabilities","D":"depleting assets"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Cash in hand and at bank, plus debtors are components of current assets. Current assets are all assets of a business that are expected to be used up or converted into cash within one business operating cycle \u2013 typically 12 months. They include cash, stocks, debtors, and prepaid expenses.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>17","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"PURCHASES AND SALES OF GOODS : TERMS OF TRADE","question":"Goods sold under a distinctive trademark are","images":[],"options":{"A":"branded goods","B":"unsought goods","C":"perishable goods","D":"public goods"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Goods sold under a distinctive trademark are branded goods. A brand is a name, term, design, symbol, or any other feature that identifies one seller's good or service as distinct from those of other sellers. Branded goods are those that are associated with a specific, well-known brand.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>18","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"TRADE : FOREIGN TRADE","question":"A firm which imports goods with the view of re-exporting them is engaged in","images":[],"options":{"A":"bilateral trade","B":"entrepot trade","C":"multilateral trade","D":"counter trade"},"answer":"B","explanation":"A firm which imports goods with the view of re-exporting them is engaged in entrepot trade. Entrepot trade is a form of international trade in which goods are imported for the purpose of re-exporting them, rather than for domestic consumption. The goods are often stored, repackaged or processed in some way before being re-exported.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>19","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: INSURANCE : TYPES","question":"A risk whose probability of occurrence is impossible to estimate is","images":[],"options":{"A":"uninsurable risk","B":"pure risk","C":"particular risk","D":"insurable risk"},"answer":"A","explanation":"An uninsurable risk is a risk that is not insurable, typically because the likelihood of the risk occurring is unknown or it's so high that insuring it would be impractical. This is the case when the probability of occurrence is impossible to estimate.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>20","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: BANKING : SERVICES & CHALLENGES","question":"An instruction to a bank to make regular payment to a third party on behalf of a customer is","images":[],"options":{"A":"standing order","B":"money order","C":"money transfer","D":"credit transfer"},"answer":"A","explanation":"A standing order is an instruction a bank account holder gives to their bank to pay a set amount at regular intervals to another's account. The other options do not involve regular payments.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>21","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: BANKING : SERVICES & CHALLENGES","question":"Use the diagram above to answer this question    The diagram above shows a","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"standing order","B":"receipt","C":"cheque","D":"bill of exchange"},"answer":"C","explanation":"The diagram above depicts(represent) a cheque. It is a negotiable instrument.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>22","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: BANKING : SERVICES & CHALLENGES","question":"Use the diagram above to answer this question  XYZ Bank of Commerce PLC is the","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"payee","B":"endorser","C":"drawer","D":"drawee"},"answer":"D","explanation":"XYZ Bank of Commerce PLC is the drawee, the person whose name is on the cheque such payer said y is payee and the person who write the cheque is known as Drawer.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>23","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: BANKING : SERVICES & CHALLENGES","question":"Use the diagram above to answer this question  Oki Williams is the","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"payee","B":"endorser","C":"drawer","D":"drawee"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Oki williams is drawer, his the owner of the account and who issue the cheque.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>24","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"TRADE : FOREIGN TRADE","question":"An international trade practice where goods are exchanged for other good is","images":[],"options":{"A":"entrepot trade","B":"bilateral trade","C":"barter trade","D":"counter trade"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Barter trade is a system in the economy that involves the exchange of goods and services for other goods and services. This is an ancient method of trade and exchange. The other options involve monetary transactions.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>25","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: BANKING : SERVICES & CHALLENGES","question":"A proportion of the total deposit that a commercial bank must keep as cash and convertible papers is","images":[],"options":{"A":"special deposit","B":"liquidity ratio","C":"interest rate","D":"bank rate"},"answer":"B","explanation":"The proportion of the total deposit that a commercial bank must keep as cash and convertible papers is known as the liquidity ratio. This is a financial metric used to determine a bank's ability to pay off its short-term debts obligations. The liquidity ratio shows the proportion of a company's short-term assets available to cover its short-term liabilities.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>26","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: INSURANCE : PRINCIPLES","question":"The principle that applies when Greene and Sunwar Insurance Companies jointly indemnified Fatou for the destruction of her storey building by fire is","images":[],"options":{"A":"contribution","B":"insurable interest","C":"proximate cause","D":"subrogation"},"answer":"A","explanation":"The principle that applies when two insurance companies jointly indemnify a person for a loss is known as the principle of contribution. This principle is used when the insured has taken out more than one insurance policy on the same subject matter. In such a case, each insurer contributes proportionately to the loss.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>27","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"STOCK EXCHANGE : PROCEDURES OF TRANSACTIONS","question":"The charge paid by a specular for non-settlement of his account within the specified period is","images":[],"options":{"A":"backwardation","B":"brokerage","C":"commission","D":"contango"},"answer":"B","explanation":"This refers to the fee or commission charged by a broker for executing transactions or providing services. In some contexts, it can include additional charges for non-settlement or late settlement of accounts.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>28","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: BANKING : SERVICES & CHALLENGES","question":"A cheque for which payment is refused due to insufficient funds is a","images":[],"options":{"A":"bearer cheque","B":"crossed cheque","C":"dishonoured cheque","D":"stale cheque"},"answer":"C","explanation":"A dishonoured cheque is a cheque that the bank has refused to honour as there is insufficient funds in the account, or there is some other problem with the cheque. A bearer cheque is a cheque that is payable to whoever presents it at the bank. A crossed cheque is a cheque that is marked specifying an instruction about the way it is to be redeemed. A stale cheque is a cheque that is presented for payment six months after its date of issue.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>29","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: COMMUNICATION : TYPES","question":"The keyboard of a computer is classified as","images":[],"options":{"A":"an input device","B":"a memory device","C":"an output device","D":"a storage device"},"answer":"A","explanation":"The keyboard of a computer is an input device. It is used to input data into the computer. A memory device is a device that is used to store data or information. An output device is a device that outputs data from the computer. A storage device is a device that is used to store data or information for a long period of time.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>30","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: COMMUNICATION : TYPES","question":"A communication equipment which is stationed in space for sending signals is","images":[],"options":{"A":"data processor","B":"internet","C":"satellite","D":"telex machine"},"answer":"C","explanation":"A satellite is a communication equipment which is stationed in space for sending signals. A data processor is a system which processes data. The internet is a global network of computers. A telex machine is a communication device that was used to send and receive messages over long distances.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>31","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: TRANSPORTATION : MEANING AND TYPES OF TRANSPORTATION","question":"One of the factors which determines the choice of transport for goods is the","images":[],"options":{"A":"cost of purchasing the mode of transport","B":"maintenance cost of the mode of transport","C":"number of users of the mode of transport","D":"nature of the goods to be transported"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The nature of the goods to be transported is a key factor in determining the choice of transport. Different goods require different modes of transport based on their size, weight, perishability, and other factors. For instance, perishable goods like fruits and vegetables might require refrigerated transport, while large, heavy goods might require transport by ship or train.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>32","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: ADVERTISING : ADVANTAGES AND DISADVANTAGES","question":"Which of the following activities increase demand for goods and services?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Advertising","B":"Banking","C":"Transportation","D":"Warehousing"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Advertising is a marketing activity that increases demand for goods and services. It does this by making consumers aware of a product or service, highlighting its benefits, and persuading consumers to purchase it. Banking, transportation, and warehousing are all important aspects of commerce, but they do not directly increase demand for goods and services.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>33","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"ELEMENTS OF BUSINESS MANAGEMENT : ORGANIZATIONAL STRUCTURE","question":"A diagram showing the positions of the structure of a company is","images":[],"options":{"A":"span of control","B":"organizational chart","C":"vertical integration","D":"flow chart"},"answer":"B","explanation":"An organizational chart is a diagram that shows the structure of a company, including the positions and relationships between different parts of the organization. It provides a visual representation of the hierarchy within the company and can help employees understand their role within the larger structure. A span of control refers to the number of subordinates a manager or supervisor can effectively manage. Vertical integration is a strategy where a company takes control of more than one stage in the production or distribution of a product. A flow chart is a type of diagram that represents a process, showing the steps as boxes of various kinds, and their order by connecting them with arrows.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>34","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"ELEMENT OF MARKETING : PUBLIC RELATION & CUSTOMER SERVICE","question":"Good consumer service practise requires","images":[],"options":{"A":"charging high prices so as to make profit","B":"hanging up customers' phone calls when busy","C":"patience towards ill-mannered customers","D":"promoting hard working employees"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Good consumer service practice requires patience towards ill-mannered customers. This is because customer service is about dealing with customers in a polite, respectful, and helpful manner, regardless of their behavior. It's about understanding and meeting their needs and expectations, and handling complaints and problems effectively.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>35","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"LEGAL ASPECT OF BUSINESS: CONTRACT : ELEMENT OF A VALID CONTRACT","question":"The elements of a contract are offer ,","images":[],"options":{"A":"acceptance and performance","B":"consideration and performance","C":"legality and formality","D":"acceptance and consideration"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The elements of a contract are offer, acceptance, and consideration. An offer is a proposal by one party to another to enter into a contract. Acceptance is the agreement by the other party to the offer. Consideration is something of value that is given in exchange for something else. It is the price paid for the promise of the other party.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>36","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: ADVERTISING : TYPES AND MEDIA","question":"Which of the following types of advertising is aimed at taking away existing buyers from their suppliers?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Negative","B":"Competitive","C":"Informative","D":"Mass"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Competitive advertising is aimed at taking away existing buyers from their suppliers. This type of advertising is used by companies to differentiate their products or services from those of their competitors. It is designed to highlight the unique features and benefits of a company's product or service, and to persuade customers to switch from their current supplier to the company.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>37","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"ELEMENT OF MARKETING : THE MARKETING CONCEPT","question":"The marketing concept emphasizes the need to","images":[],"options":{"A":"identify and satisfy customer wants","B":"maximize foreign investment","C":"maximise profit for the company","D":"build a strong and solid brand"},"answer":"A","explanation":"The marketing concept is a business philosophy that emphasizes the importance of creating value for customers. It involves identifying the needs and wants of the target market and delivering the desired satisfactions more effectively and efficiently than competitors. Therefore, the correct answer is 'identify and satisfy customer wants'.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>38","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"LEGAL ASPECT OF BUSINESS: SALES OF GOODS ACT : AGENCY IN SALES OF GOODS ACT","question":"An agent whose authority, as conferred by the principal, has no limit is a","images":[],"options":{"A":"del credere agent","B":"general agent","C":"special agent","D":"universal agent"},"answer":"D","explanation":"An agent whose authority, as conferred by the principal, has no limit is a universal agent. A universal agent can perform all acts that can be lawfully delegated to an agency. This is different from a general agent who can only perform acts related to a business or employment, and a special agent who is authorized to conduct a single transaction or a series of transactions not involving continuity of service.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>39","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"LEGAL ASPECT OF BUSINESS: HIRE PURCHASES : MEANING AND TYPES","question":"An agreement in which Philip paid half the price of a car and accepted to pay the rest in installments is a","images":[],"options":{"A":"conditional sale contract","B":"credit sale contract","C":"hire purchase contract","D":"haulage contract"},"answer":"C","explanation":"A hire purchase contract is a type of agreement where a customer agrees to pay for goods in parts or a percentage at a time. In this case, Philip paid half the price of a car and accepted to pay the rest in installments, which is a characteristic of a hire purchase contract. A conditional sale contract would involve the transfer of ownership after certain conditions are met, and a credit sale contract would involve the immediate transfer of ownership with payment to be made in the future. A haulage contract is unrelated to this scenario as it involves the transportation of goods.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>40","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"LEGAL ASPECT OF BUSINESS: CONTRACT : MEANING AND TYPES OF CONTRACT","question":"A new offer of contract that terminates the original offer is","images":[],"options":{"A":"a void contract","B":"a counter offer","C":"an invalid offer","D":"quasi contract"},"answer":"B","explanation":"A counter offer is a response given to an initial offer. It means the original offer has been rejected and replaced by a new one. Therefore, it terminates the original offer. A void contract is a contract that is not legally enforceable. An invalid offer is an offer that does not meet the legal requirements for a valid contract. A quasi contract is a contract created by a court in the interests of fairness and justice.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>41","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"ELEMENTS OF BUSINESS MANAGEMENT : ORGANIZATIONAL STRUCTURE","question":"Which of the following roles is performed by middle management in an organization?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Formulation of objectives and strategies","B":"Review of master plans, programmes and budgets","C":"Review and appraisal of operational results","D":"Implementation of organizational plans and objectives"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Middle management in an organization is responsible for implementing the plans and objectives set by the top management. They do not formulate objectives and strategies, this is the role of top management. Review of master plans, programmes and budgets is also a role of top management. Review and appraisal of operational results is a role of both middle and top management, but it is not the primary role of middle management.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>42","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"ELEMENTS OF BUSINESS MANAGEMENT : PRINCIPLE","question":"The management term which refers to the number of staff a superior officer can efficiently supervise is","images":[],"options":{"A":"delegation of authority","B":"division of labour","C":"unity of command","D":"span of control"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Span of control refers to the number of subordinates that a manager or supervisor can effectively manage. This number varies depending on the complexity of tasks, the abilities of the manager and the abilities of the workers. Delegation of authority is the process of distributing and entrusting work to other members of an organization. Division of labour refers to the assignment of different parts of a manufacturing process or task to different individuals. Unity of command is a principle that suggests that an individual should only report to one manager.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>43","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS UNIT: PUBLIC CORPORATION : MEANING AND TYPES","question":"Which of the following business units could be commercialized?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Public corporation","B":"Cooperative society","C":"Private company","D":"Sole proprietorship"},"answer":"A","explanation":"A public company and a private company can be commercialized. However, the term \"commercialized\" typically refers to the process of bringing a product or service to market. In the context of business units, the term might be more relevant to the activities they engage in rather than their classification as public or private.    Public Company: A company whose shares are traded publicly on stock exchanges. These companies are already commercialized in the sense that they offer their shares to the public and engage in business activities to generate profit.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>44","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS UNIT: PUBLIC CORPORATION : ADVANTAGES AND DISADVANTAGES","question":"The restructuring of a government enterprise with the intention of making it profit oriented is","images":[],"options":{"A":"privatization","B":"nationalization","C":"commercialization","D":"deregulation"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Commercialization is the process of converting a government owned company to profit oriented. It is the restructuring of a government enterprise with the intention of making it profit oriented.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>45","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"ECONOMIC GROUPING : MEANING AND TYPES SUCH AS ECOWAS, NIGER BASIN COM ETC.","question":"The headquarters of the Mano River Union is in","images":[],"options":{"A":"Freetown","B":"Monrovia","C":"Conakry","D":"Abidjan"},"answer":"A","explanation":"The headquarters of the Mano River Union is in Free town, Sierra Leone. The Mano River Union (MRU) is an international association initially established between Liberia and Sierra Leone in 1973 for economic and social development. Guinea joined in 1980 and C\u00f4te d'Ivoire in 2008. The MRU is named for the Mano River which begins in the Guinea highlands and forms a border between Liberia and Sierra Leone.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>46","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS CAPITAL, PROFIT AND TURNOVER : SOURCE OF FINANCE","question":"A source of capital to a public company which attracts a fixed rate of interest is","images":[],"options":{"A":"an ordinary share","B":"a subvention","C":"a debenture","D":"an overdraft"},"answer":"C","explanation":"A debenture is a type of debt instrument that is not secured by physical assets or collateral. Debentures are backed only by the general creditworthiness and reputation of the issuer. Both corporations and governments frequently issue this type of bond to secure capital. Like other types of bonds, debentures are documented in an indenture. Debentures have a fixed rate of interest.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>47","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"ECONOMIC GROUPING : MEANING AND TYPES SUCH AS ECOWAS, NIGER BASIN COM ETC.","question":"Which of the following is not an economic grouping in West Africa?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Lake Chad Basin Commission","B":"Economic Community of West African States","C":"European Union","D":"Niger Basin Commission"},"answer":"C","explanation":"The European Union is not an economic grouping in West Africa. It is a political and economic union of 27 member states that are located primarily in Europe. The other options, Lake Chad Basin Commission, Economic Community of West African States, and Niger Basin Commission, are all economic groupings in West Africa.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>48","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"AIDS TO TRADE: BANKING : SERVICES & CHALLENGES","question":"A customer who wishes to withdraw an amount greater than the balance in his current account would apply for","images":[],"options":{"A":"a standing order","B":"an overdraft","C":"a loan","D":"a credit transfer"},"answer":"B","explanation":"An overdraft is a facility provided by the bank to its customers that allows the customer to withdraw money from their account even if the account balance is zero, or less than the amount they want to withdraw. This is a form of short-term borrowing facility provided by the bank to its customers. A loan, on the other hand, is a long-term borrowing. A standing order is an instruction to the bank to make regular fixed payments to a particular person or organization, and a credit transfer is a deposit of funds directly into a bank account.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>49","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS UNIT: MERGER : MEANING AND TYPES OF MERGER","question":"The combination of business activities of Abbas Ltd and Denko Ltd to form one large company is","images":[],"options":{"A":"an amalgamation","B":"a consortium","C":"an acquisition","D":"a cartel"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Amalgamation is the process of combining two or more companies into a larger single company. In this case, Abbas Ltd and Denko Ltd are combining to form one large company, which is a clear example of an amalgamation.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Commerce>2019>50","subject":"Commerce","year":"2019","type":"Objective","topic":"BUSINESS UNIT: PUBLIC CORPORATION : ADVANTAGES AND DISADVANTAGES","question":"The difference between commercialization and privatization is that commercialized businesses","images":[],"options":{"A":"are government-owned while privatized businesses are owned by individuals","B":"are non-profit marking ventures while privatized businesses are profit oriented","C":"can sell shares while privatized businesses cannot","D":"employed more workers than privatized businesses"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Commercialization and privatization are two different concepts. Commercialization refers to the process of managing or running something principally for financial gain, or the process of incorporating an activity into the economy. These businesses are typically government-owned. On the other hand, privatization is the process of transferring an enterprise or industry from the public sector to the private sector. The businesses are owned by individuals or a group of individuals.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"}];